(219, 1, '2023-09-19 10:37:15', '2023-09-19 10:37:15', '<!-- wp:heading {\"textAlign\":\"center\",\"level\":1} -->\n<h1 class=\"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center\"><strong><strong>VALORANT Champions Tour 2023: Masters Tokyo  Showmatch</strong></strong></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":218,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img src=\"http://localhost:8800/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/737px-VCT_Masters_Tokyo_allmode.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-218\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Valorant Champions Tour (VCT) 2023 Masters Tokyo is currently underway with eight teams battling it out in the playoffs. The teams are fighting for glory, bragging rights along with a massive total prize pool of $1 Million USD. The playoffs stage commenced on 16th June and is set to conclude on 25th June, with the best-of-five (BO5) grand finals. This tournament is high stakes since the winner grants its region an extra slot for Valorant Champions 2023 from the respective Last Chance Qualifier.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, there is more to the event than just these playoff matches. On 17th June, Riot Games announced that this Masters will also feature a showmatch,</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>showcasing the newest Valorant game mode: Team Deathmatch.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:buttons {\"align\":\"wide\",\"layout\":{\"type\":\"flex\",\"justifyContent\":\"center\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons alignwide\"><!-- wp:button /--></div>\n<!-- /wp:buttons -->', 'Masters Tokyo 2023', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '20-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-09-19 10:37:15', '2023-09-19 10:37:15', '', 20, 'http://localhost:8800/?p=219', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
